article.description: Jadrian Clark threw a 60-yard pass to Darryl Denby with 31 seconds to play to preserve Weber State's unbeaten conference record with a 37-36 win over Southern Utah Saturday night.
article.headline: Clark hits Denby for 37-36 Weber St win over Southern Utah
article.linkText: Clark hits Denby for 37-36 Weber St win over Southern Utah
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Jadrian Clark threw a 60-yard pass to Darryl Denby with 31 seconds to play to preserve Weber State's unbeaten conference record with a 37-36 win over Southern Utah Saturday night. Clark's game-winning throw capped a fourth-quarter rally that brought the Wildcats (5-2, 4-0 Big Sky) back from a 23-point deficit. Earlier, Stefan Cantwell ran for a 10-yard touchdown and Clark threw an 11-yard score to Andrew Vollert to close the Southern Utah lead to 36-30 with 2:21 remaining. Clark had 436 yards and four touchdowns on 31-of-52 passing. Haini Moimoi had 126 yards receiving and Denby 90 yards and a score. Jacob DeMaio's 91-yard punt in the first quarter set a new school record. Southern Utah's Patrick Tyler threw for two touchdowns in the first half and ran for another to help the Thunderbirds (3-4, 2-3) to a 23-6 halftime lead. Tyler had 239 yards and two scores passing and two rushing TDs.
